[[Baron]] '''Notluwiski Papanoida''', a [[Pantoran]] [[Gender|male]], was the [[chairman]] of the [[moon]] [[Pantora]] during the final years of the [[Galactic Republic]]. Papanoida was a powerful figure according to his daughter [[Senator]] [[Chi Eekway Papanoida|Chi Eekway]]. Toward the end of the [[Clone Wars]], Papanoida and his daughter were present in a [[Coruscant]] opera house when [[Anakin Skywalker]] met with [[Supreme Chancellor]] [[Darth Sidious|Sheev Palpatine]].

==Biography==
Notluwiski Papanoida<ref name="SW Kids">{{SWKidsYouTube|series=Star Wars Full Circle|text=X-wing|video=Z_kxccFE7nQ|nolive=1}}</ref> was a [[Pantoran]] [[Gender|male]] who [[Homeworld|hailed]] from the [[moon]] [[Pantora]].<ref name="Encyclopedia" /> The Pantoran fathered several children, including [[Ion Papanoida|Ion]], [[Che Amanwe Papanoida|Che Amanwe]], and [[Chi Eekway Papanoida|Chi Eekway]].<ref name="SOI" /> Prior to assuming the role of [[Supreme Chairman]] of the [[Pantoran Assembly]], Papanoida was a wealthy and well-connected media mogul popular with the people of Pantora. A memorable character in Pantoran society, he had little difficulty cementing himself as a popular choice to take the position of chairman.<ref name="BMF 85">{{BuildFalconCite|85|Guide to the Galaxy}}</ref>

[[File:PapanoidaPantoraOffice-SoI.png|thumb|left|250px|Chairman Papanoida working in his office on Pantora]]
After the [[death]] of [[Chairman]] [[Chi Cho]] during a [[One-Day War|conflict]] on the [[Water|ice]] [[planet]] [[Orto Plutonia]] during the time of the [[Clone Wars]],<ref name="Trespass">{{TCW|Trespass}}</ref> Papanoida was sworn in as Pantora's new chairman.<ref name="Encyclopedia" /> When the [[Trade Federation]] [[Blockade of Pantora|blockaded]] Pantora, public unrest threatened to force the moon to secede from the [[Galactic Republic]] and join the [[Confederacy of Independent Systems|Confederacy]], who were offering aid. Papanoida relied on [[Senator]] [[Riyo Chuchi]] to plead for assistance in the [[Galactic Senate|Senate]] in ending the [[blockade]]. However, the Federation had his two daughters kidnapped as leverage. Papanoida could guess that his daughters might be on the [[Lucrehulk-class battleship|Droid Control Ship]] blockading Pantora and dispatched Chuchi and [[Jedi]] [[Padawan]] [[Ahsoka Tano]] to go there under the pretense of a diplomatic mission, while he and his son investigate on their own. Whereas the [[Coruscant Security Force]] failed to find any clues in his quarters, Papanoida discovered that one of his [[Icon of the Moon Goddess|idols]] was misplaced and smeared with blood. Analyzing the blood, he found that it belonged to a [[Rodian]] [[bounty hunter]] named [[Greedo]].<ref name="SOI" />

[[File:PapanoidaTheCloneWars.jpg|thumb|right|250px|Papanoida during the fight]]
The Pantorans traveled to the [[Boba Fett's Palace|palace]] of [[Jabba Desilijic Tiure]] on [[Tatooine]], whom Greedo was employed by. Papanoida was able to draw the Rodian out by simply telling a [[Trella Bare'Ah|female Twi'lek]] that they were looking for him. As expected, Greedo came to the Pantorans and attempted to get rid of them, only for Papanoida to pull out a knife and hold it against Greedo's throat. Matters were brought before Jabba, whom Papanoida reasoned with into assisting them, by comparing Greedo's blood to the sample he found on Coruscant. No sooner than Jabba permitted it did Greedo spill that he had Chi Eekway held in [[Mos Eisley]]. The Pantorans forced Greedo to lead them to the [[Chalmun's Spaceport Cantina|cantina]] where Eekway was being held. But things got tense, as Greedo's [[Gotal]] partner began to question him. The Rodian turned on the Pantorans and fled the cantina, as all the patrons started firing on them. The Pantorans were able to dispatch all the assailants; Eekway even saved her father's life by shooting the Gotal when he attempted to kill Papanoida when his back was turned. The Pantorans returned to Coruscant as Chuchi and Tano rescued Che Amanwe from the Droid Control Ship. Because the Federation lacked leverage, they were forced to end the blockade of Pantora.<ref name="SOI" />

By the end of the Clone Wars, Papanoida and his daughter Chi Eekway were present in the [[Coruscant]] opera house following the [[Battle of Coruscant]]. The two stood outside [[Supreme Chancellor]] [[Darth Sidious|Sheev Palpatine's]] seating box when [[Anakin Skywalker]] came to visit Palpatine.<ref name="ROTS">{{Film|III}}</ref>

==Personality and traits==
[[File:N_Papanoida_And_His_Family.png|thumb|left|180px|Papanoida with his family]]
The chairman of his homeworld [[Pantora]], Papanoida stood at 1.77 [[meter]]s tall, or 5 [[Foot|feet]], 10 inches. He had [[Color|blue]] skin, white hair, and brown eyes.<ref name="Join the Battle" /> He was an ally of the Republic, but was primarily focused on the governing of his people.<ref name="VE">''[[Star Wars: The Visual Encyclopedia]]''</ref> He was also very crafty, knowing the best way to find Greedo was to allow the Rodian to attack him in public. He was also a wise negotiator, as he successfully implored Jabba the Hutt to listen to his requests by emphasizing they were fellow fathers who would do anything to save their children. Although he was a kind and caring family man, he was also a skilled combatant, wielding two blaster pistols capably during a shootout on [[Tatooine]].<ref name="SOI" />

==Equipment==
Papanoida wore a [[Color|purple]] Pantoran coat with a matching [[hat]] along with a black [[belt]], [[cane]], and [[boot]]s.<ref name="VE" /> He also had a knife hidden in his coat and was comfortable in a gunfight, capably wielding two blaster pistols when a confrontation inside [[Chalmun's Spaceport Cantina]] escalated.<ref name="SOI" />

==Behind the scenes==
Baron Papanoida was played by ''[[Star Wars]]'' creator [[George Lucas]] in [[Star Wars: Episode III Revenge of the Sith|''Revenge of the Sith'']].<ref name="ROTS" /> He was voiced by [[Corey Burton]] in the ''[[Star Wars: The Clone Wars]]'' episode "[[Sphere of Influence]],"<ref name="SOI" /> who based his voice on the legendary director and actor [[Wikipedia:Orson Welles|Orson Welles]].<ref name="Trivia">{{SW|url=series/clone-wars/sphere-of-influence-trivia-gallery|text="Sphere of Influence" Trivia Gallery}} {{C|Slide 1}}</ref>

